					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79054379" rend="visible">
						<summary>The first volume of the Bible with masorah magna and parva.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79054379">
							<locus from="1r" to="258v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tana&quot;kh</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תנ"ך</title>
							<decoNote type="initial">Initial-word panels with penwork decoration, inhabited.<locus n="1r, 34v, 63r, 83r, 110v, 137r, 155r, 172v, 215v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="miniature">Menorah, in colours.<locus n="136r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="border">Full border.<locus n="1r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">
								<locus n="86r, 90r"/>2 unfinished foliate scrolls around initial-word panels.</decoNote>
							<note>
								<p>First of the two uniform volumes of the Hebrew Bible, the other being Harley 5711, see <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">54</ref>; consists of Pentateuch and Former Prophets. </p>
								<p>See <ref target="Tahan_2007" type="page">30</ref>, <ref target="Wright_1972" type="page">254&amp;461</ref>, <ref target="Wright_1966" type="page">227</ref>, <ref target="Narkiss_1984" type="page">57</ref>, <ref target="Metzger_1982" type="page">304</ref>, <ref target="Ebenbauer_1991" type="page">131-150</ref>. </p>
							</note>
